claim.claim-text:
A refrigerator (1) comprising:
an inner case (20) comprising an ice making chamber (70) formed in an interior of the inner case;
an outer case (30) coupled to an outside of the inner case (20);
a body insulator (40) foamed between the inner case (20) and the outer case (30);
a refrigerant pipe (210) having at least a portion disposed in the ice making chamber (70), to supply cooling energy to the ice making chamber; and
a refrigerant pipe insulator (300) enclosing at least a portion of the refrigerant pipe (210), to insulate and support the refrigerant pipe,
wherein the inner case (20) further comprises an opening (29) allowing the refrigerant pipe insulator (300) to extend therethrough,
wherein the refrigerant pipe insulator (300) extends through the opening (29) such that an inserted portion (301) of the refrigerant pipe insulator is disposed in the ice making chamber, and a remaining or fixed portion (302) of the refrigerant pipe insulator is disposed between the inner case (20) and the outer case (30), and
wherein the refrigerant pipe insulator (300) is supported by the body insulator (40) foamed between the inner case and the outer case.

A method of manufacturing a refrigerator (1), comprising:
preparing (610) an inner case (20) including an ice making chamber (70) and an opening (29) communicating with the ice making chamber;
preparing (610) an outer case (30) to be coupled to an outside of the inner case (20);
preparing (620) a refrigerant pipe assembly (110) including a refrigerant pipe (210) having at least a portion to be disposed in the ice making chamber (70) so as to supply cooling energy to the ice making chamber, and a refrigerant pipe insulator (300) to insulate the refrigerant pipe;
inserting (630) the refrigerant pipe assembly (110) into the opening (29) of the inner case (20) in an inward direction from the outside of the inner case such that a portion (301) of the refrigerant pipe insulator is disposed in the ice making chamber, and a remaining portion (302) of the refrigerant pipe insulator (300) is disposed between the inner case (20) and the outer case (130); and
foaming (650) a body insulator (40) between the inner case (20) and the outer case (30), thereby supporting the refrigerant pipe insulator by the body insulator.

The method according to claim 16, wherein the preparing the refrigerant pipe assembly further comprises:
preparing at least one clamp member to couple the first and second insulator sections;

and
coupling the at least one clamp member (400) to the first and second insulator sections (310, 320);
